[lesson]   Solution: FIX_PLAN: (1) In `auto_round/utils/model.py`, after the download resolves `model_path` and the function reads `config.json` for MM_KEYS scanning, also re-evaluate `config.model_type` against `_LLM_ONLY_MODEL_TYPES` — when the model_type matches, force `result = False` so the repo-ID path can no longer mis-tag gemma4_assistant as MLLM. (2) In `phases/quantize.py`, auto-enable `model_free=True` for any model whose `model_type` matches a small set including `gemma4_assistant` so AutoRound bypasses the broken Gemma4AssistantForCausalLM.forward entirely (ModelFreeCompressor reads safetensors shards directly).;SMOKE_TEST: python3 -c "from auto_round.utils.model import is_mllm_model; print('is_mllm:', is_mllm_model('google/gemma-4-E2B-it-qat-q4_0-unquantized-assistant')); assert is_mllm_model('google/gemma-4-E2B-it-qat-q4_0-unquantized-assistant') is False";```;The `_is_mllm_model` classification fix works for the HF repo ID path. Now let me verify the second part of the fix — that `phases/quantize.py` correctly auto-enables `model_free=True` for this model type.;
